1. *Ruž*a je cvet koji je poznat po svojoj lepoti. (*Ruž*a - noun, meaning "rose" - The rose is a flower known for its beauty.)
2. Volim *ruž*nu boju, jer je veoma ženstvena. (*Ruž*na - adjective, meaning "pink" - I love the pink color because it is very feminine.)
3. *Ruž*an miris se širio prostorijom. (*Ruž*an - adjective, meaning "unpleasant" - An unpleasant smell was spreading throughout the room.)
4. Sinoć sam videla *ruž*u kako se ponaša jako agresivno. (*Ruž*a - noun, meaning "a person who behaves badly" - Last night I saw a bad person acting very aggressively.)
5. Mnogo je *ruž*nih stvari koje se dešavaju u svetu. (*Ruž*nih - adjective, meaning "bad" - There are many bad things happening in the world.)
6. Kupila sam novi karmin u boji *ruž*a. (*Ruž*a - noun, meaning "lipstick" - I bought a new lipstick in the color pink.)
7. Ona je veoma *ruž*ičasta osoba, uvek je negativna. (*Ruž*ičasta - adjective, meaning "negative" - She is a very negative person.)
8. U parku je bilo mnogo prelepih *ruž*a u različitim bojama. (*Ruž*a - noun, meaning "roses" - There were many beautiful roses in different colors in the park.)
9. Nije u redu da *ruž*aš druge ljude, to je veoma nepristojno. (*Ruž*aš - verb, meaning "to insult" - It's not okay to insult other people, it's very impolite.)
10. *Ruž*i su mi omiljeni cvet, posebno crvene. (*Ruž*i - noun, meaning "roses" - Roses are my favorite flower, especially the red ones.)